4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the Alabama Brewpub Act
6 authorizes brewpubs to manufacture and sell beer for
7 on-premises consumption and to wholesalers for resale
8 under certain conditions.
9 This bill would expand and rename the law as the
10 Alabama Small Craft Alcoholic Beverages Act to include
11 small craft distilleries and small craft wineries as
12 new license categories, as well as a new small craft
13 alcoholic beverage manufacturer license that authorizes
14 a brewpub, small craft distillery, and small craft
15 winery, or any combination of these, to operate within
16 a contiguous area and sell their alcoholic beverages
17 for on-site consumption.
18 This bill would permit a brewpub, small craft
19 distillery, and small craft winery to host tours of the
20 manufacturing operation and to provide tasting samples
21 to patrons.
22 This bill would allow a brewpub, small craft
23 distillery, or small craft winery to sell products for
24 consumption off-premises at a limited number of public
25 events.
26 This bill would further allow a brewpub, small
27 craft distillery, small craft winery, or any licensed
28 manufacturer of alcoholic beverages, to maintain a
Page 1

manufacturer of alcoholic beverages, to maintain a
HB593 INTRODUCED
29 storage extension separate from the licensed
30 manufacturing premises.
31 This bill would also set qualifications for
32 licensure and would authorize the Alcoholic Beverage
33 Control Board to administer and enforce the act.
34
35
36 A BILL
37 TO BE ENTITLED
38 AN ACT
39
40 Relating to alcoholic beverages; to amend Sections
41 28-4A-1 through 28-4A-6, Code of Alabama 1975, and redesignate
42 these sections as Article 1 of Chapter 4A of Title 28, Code of
43 Alabama 1975; to add Sections 28-4A-7, 28-4A-8, 28-4A-9 to
44 Article 1 of Chapter 4A of Title 28, Code of Alabama 1975; to
45 add Articles 2, 3, and 4 to Chapter 4A of Title 28, Code of
46 Alabama 1975; to create the Alabama Small Craft Alcoholic
47 Beverages Act; to create new categories of licenses for small
48 craft distilleries and small craft wineries and create a new
49 license for small craft alcoholic beverage manufacturers that
50 operate a brewpub, small craft winery, or small craft
51 distillery or any combination of these; to provide for
52 qualifications and license requirements; to permit a brewpub,
53 small craft winery, or small craft distillery to allow tours
54 of their manufacturing facilities; to provide for sales by a
55 brewpub, small craft winery, or small craft distillery, at
56 off-premises events open to the public; to provide that a
Page 2

off-premises events open to the public; to provide that a
HB593 INTRODUCED
57 brewpub, small craft winery, or small craft distillery, or any
58 other alcoholic beverage manufacturer, may maintain a storage
59 facility off the licensed manufacturing premises; to require
60 the Alcoholic Beverage Control Board to administer and enforce
61 the act; and to amend Section 28-3A-13.1, Code of Alabama
62 1975, to make conforming changes.
63 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
